                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 8.536,
                                "byte_start": 80634,
                                "byte_stop": 114802,
                                "text": "The opinion of the Court in No. 95-26, Markman versus Westview Instruments will be announced by Justice Souter."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 8.536,
                        "stop": 176.013,
                        "byte_start": 114802,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15042,
                            "name": "David H. Souter",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/david_h_souter",
                            "last_name": "Souter",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2686,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 655362000,
                                    "date_end": 1246251600,
                                    "appointing_president": "George H. W. Bush",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2686"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32703,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 42141,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/david_souter.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 6839,
                            "identifier": "david_h_souter"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 8.536,
                                "stop": 12.659,
                                "byte_start": 114802,
                                "byte_stop": 131312,
                                "text": "This case comes to us on writ of certiorari to the Court of Appeals for the Federal Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 12.659,
                                "stop": 18.079,
                                "byte_start": 131312,
                                "byte_stop": 153045,
                                "text": "It is not as exciting as the one that Justice Ginsburg has just described to us."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 18.079,
                                "stop": 37.61,
                                "byte_start": 153045,
                                "byte_stop": 231099,
                                "text": "The issue is whether the construction of a patent falls exclusively within the province of the court, and specifically whether the Seventh Amendment requires that a jury decides meaning of disputed terms of art within the patent claim, the portion of the patent document that defines the patentee\u2019s rights."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 37.61,
                                "stop": 45.226,
                                "byte_start": 231099,
                                "byte_stop": 261610,
                                "text": "The petitioner Markman owns a patent to a system that keeps track of clothing as it moves through the dry-cleaning process."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 45.226,
                                "stop": 51.953,
                                "byte_start": 261610,
                                "byte_stop": 288464,
                                "text": "Markman sued the respondent Westview Instruments alleging that Westview\u2019s products infringe the patent."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 51.953,
                                "stop": 70.12,
                                "byte_start": 288464,
                                "byte_stop": 361189,
                                "text": "Although the jury found that it did infringed it, the District Court granted the directive verdict nonetheless on the ground that Westview\u2019s device in contrast to Markman\u2019s is unable to track what was described as inventory as that word is used in the patent claim."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 70.12,
                                "stop": 80.745,
                                "byte_start": 361189,
                                "byte_stop": 403716,
                                "text": "Markman appealed arguing that the Seventh Amendment required the jury not to judge to interpret the term inventory when, as here, evidences introduced to trial without its meaning."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 80.745,
                                "stop": 86.802,
                                "byte_start": 403716,
                                "byte_stop": 427854,
                                "text": "The Court of Appeals affirmed holding that it was consistent with the Seventh Amendment the judges construe patent term."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 86.802,
                                "stop": 92.643,
                                "byte_start": 427854,
                                "byte_stop": 451259,
                                "text": "In an opinion filed with the Clerk of Court today, we affirm the judgment of the Court of Appeals."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 92.643,
                                "stop": 107.177,
                                "byte_start": 451259,
                                "byte_stop": 509356,
                                "text": "The Seventh Amendment right of trial by jury is the right which existed under the English common law when the amendment was adapted and we therefore looked to 18th century practice to assess the substance of the common law right that the Seventh Amendment was intended to preserve."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 107.177,
                                "stop": 127.774,
                                "byte_start": 509356,
                                "byte_stop": 591798,
                                "text": "Given that infringement case arise they were at the time of the founding, tried before a jury, we have to determine whether particular trial issue, here a patent claim construction, must be decided by jury in order to preserve the essence of the right to a jury trial that existed at the appropriate time."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 127.774,
                                "stop": 141.819,
                                "byte_start": 591798,
                                "byte_stop": 648014,
                                "text": "There is no direct antecedent to modern claim construction in the historical sources and 18th century patent cases reveal no analogous practice supporting the Markman\u2019s contention that juries construed the terms of the patent."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 141.819,
                                "stop": 147.774,
                                "byte_start": 648014,
                                "byte_stop": 671733,
                                "text": "To the extent that any analog responsible it seems to work against Markman\u2019s position in fact."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 147.774,
                                "stop": 154.774,
                                "byte_start": 671733,
                                "byte_stop": 699736,
                                "text": "Accordingly we look elsewhere to characterize this issue in order to allocate it as between judge and jury."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 154.774,
                                "stop": 165.819,
                                "byte_start": 699736,
                                "byte_stop": 743935,
                                "text": "When we do existing precedents, the relative interpretive skills of judges and juries, and the statutory policy considerations to all favor allocating this position to the judge."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 165.819,
                                "stop": 173.783,
                                "byte_start": 743935,
                                "byte_stop": 775805,
                                "text": "We therefore hold that the construction of terms within a patent claim or even terms of art falls within the province of the court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 173.783,
                                "stop": 176.013,
                                "byte_start": 775805,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Our opinion is unanimous."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
